@translation labeled en project



@(1)Say to my king, @lab{2–3}thus says Nanna-ki’a@, the frontier commander,
your servant:


@(4)Edana has turned against my king. @lab{6}Atta-mannum brought @lab{5}a 600
(man) army of Gungunum into Edana. @lab{7}(But) I prevented that army
from entering the old upper city. @lab{8}So they camped in the new city.


@(9–11)That army (of Gungunum) came from the bank of the Amar-Suena
canal in order to build brick(works), fortify Dunnum and dig a canal.


@(12–15)If my king does not issue NIM-weapons, bows, arrows, small
boats including their ﬁshermen (and) their provisions, weapons (and)
...—the arms of battle—(16)that army from the bank of the Amar-Suena
canal @lab{17}will continue building with brick(works), fortifying Dunnum
and digging canals. @lab{18}May my king not be negligent! @lab{19}It is
urgent!

