@translation labeled en project



@(2)Say @lab{1}to Nanna-ki’a@, the frontier commander, @lab{3}thus says Lipit-Ištar,
your king:


@(4)I, the king, sent you a letter about the enemy troops.^1^

@(5)Atta-mannum is someone doing well by his king. @lab{6}He is a better servant to his
king than you! @lab{7}Why is it that without me knowing it you have not
been obliging your king?^2^


@(10)Now, I am sending you post-haste @lab{8}2000 spearmen, @lab{9}2000 bowmen
(and) @lab{10}2000 axe-men. @lab{11}The enemy is camped in the new city—(12)
chase them from their positions! @lab{13}They are still carrying out the work,
so it is the case that you have not obeyed (me!).


@(14)Put guards on all the individual cities from their border up to yours.

@(15)Do not let that city out of your grasp! @lab{16}Set your soldiers there! @lab{17}It
is urgent!

^1^Var (X5): I sent word after you informed me about the troops.
^2^Var X5: (7A)Why is it that the troops there that are under my
authority have not been stationed among the people? @lab{7B}Now he (=
Atta-mannum) is stationing (his) troops there!”

