@translation labeled en project



@(1)Say to the king whose brilliance shines forth like the moon over all
the lands: @lab{3}Repeat @lab{2}to the king who renders just verdicts like Utu,
effecting decisions like Ištaran. @lab{3}to my king who hears prayers: @lab{4}Thus
says Lugal-šu,^1^ citizen of Nippur, your servant:


@(5)Like a sheep, grazing became my lot,^2^ (and) I ﬁnished by rubbing
(myself) down. @lab{6}Like an ox bound to a yoke it cannot support, I have
been sent to the desert. @lab{7}Like a cow whose calf is not by her side,^3^ I
cry plaintively. @lab{8}Like a ewe whose lamb is seized in the feeding-pen,
(my) hands are tied. @lab{9}Like a bird, I was snatched in my nest. @lab{10}Like
a boat that did not take refuge at a stable dock,^4^ the wind has cast me
adrift.


@(11)In the streets of Nippur, sorrow consumed me. @lab{12}A foreign city
has entered into my city. I had no protector. @lab{13}A foreign house has
entered into my house. It exercised authority over me. @lab{14}In my city,
like a slave, I did not carry silver. Dirty hair hung (from my) head.^5^


@(15)My friends, companions, acquaintances and dear ones @lab{16}looked
contemptuously at me like (at) a man who eats alone. @lab{17}My birth
mother, whose breasts are (like?) crescents, @lab{18}took my consumption of
milk from my mouth (as I sat) in (her) lap. @lab{19}My father, who raised
me in his lap, cast me away.


@(20)My merciful lady—her temple is precious!—no longer notices me.

@(21)Like a bad tree which has born no fruit, no one rejoices over me. @lab{22}I
am a shoot with no off-shoots, thus I do not want to be carried off!


@(23)May my king consider my case and return me to my rightful position!

^1^ Var (N13): Lugal-nesa@e.
^2^ Lit: “My mouth eating grass like a sheep appeared to me.”
^3^ Lit: “like a cow whose calf is not tied next to her.”
^4^ Lit: “like a boat that was not held back (tak4) at a stable dock.”
Var (X2): “a boat not ﬁrmly secured (kar).”
^5^ Lit: “In my city, I do not go around like (someone) free of claims. The hair of
(my) dirty head is hanging down.”
Alternate: “In my city, I go around unclean like a slave ...”



