@(1)Say to the governor and chief temple administrator, @lab{2}thus says UrEnlila:

@(3)An irrigation channel, which had been cleared, was carrying water.

@(4)(But) Enlila@u and Hanzamu @lab{5}breached it (and so) made off with
(water) from it. @lab{6}(Because of this) Lugalane said: @lab{7}“(That) single channel is for me, (that) single channel is for you (and that) single channel
is for the governor. @lab{8}Thus water will certainly be brought to each
of you.” He spoke, (but) they (i.e. Enlila@u and Hanzamu) did not
agree: @lab{9}“Your canal has no workmen, (so) its channel carries water
(unchecked).”


@(10)As for me, what escapes from it carries water to me. @lab{11}The labor
(force) is insufﬁcient for me. You should send me 5 or 10 workmen.


@(12)It is urgent!

