@translation labeled en project



@(1)Say to Di@ir-inim-siga @lab{3}thus says @lab{2}Nabi-Enlil, the scribe, the son of
Sa@-Enlila:


@(4)This is what I have done (so that) @lab{5}the youngsters would get a whiff
of Nippur!


@(6)For three years I have been replaced with someone. @lab{8}I told KANinurta @lab{7}that the place they (the youngsters) were staying was in the teacher’s house, but not only did it not seem good (enough) to me,

@(8)the person (instructing them) was incompetent as well. @lab{9}Out of regard
for my teacher’s house, I have not opened my mouth (publicly). @lab{10}Now
then, the place where they are staying is just not a proper school! @lab{11}No
one can get an education (there)! @lab{12}No one could recite (even) 20 or
30 incantations, @lab{13}nor perform 10 or 20 songs. @lab{14}(But) from the start
I did not want to open my mouth about the house of my teacher.

@(15)Didn’t you know it’s the case that the school in Nippur is unique?

@(16)He (KA-Ninurta?) told you that ... is incompetent, but you do not
appreciate the importance of his words.^1^ @lab{17}So that, to my credit, they
will be able to get a good education, @lab{18}get informed of everything that
is tested everywhere in Nippur as well as Isin! @lab{20}I will have them learn:

@(19)incantations, songs, royal inscriptions, Sumerian, panegyric, @lab{20}... up
to and including the lamentation corpus! @lab{21}I will establish it for them
in a great place, just like Nippur is! @lab{22}I will deposit [n (units)] of gold
(and) 1 talent of silver to their credit.


@(23)Do not neglect ...! @lab{24}Do not keep the kids from ... speech! @lab{25}Do
not let them bypass (any aspect of ) the curriculum! @lab{26}They should
learn ..., the alala songs, (as well as) the series izi and lú-ša. @lab{27}(If so,
then) in the future, I shall never complain again!^2^

^1^ Literally: “you leave out the importance of his mouth.” (Translation following
Attinger, personal communication).
^2^ Alternative: “then I shall never envy (Nippur) again!”

